<br>
They could move the bottleneck around, but unless they decided to up the spawn rate and let more cleric epics be completed faster, they'd have to put that bottleneck somewhere.<br>
<br>
The reason Ragefire and the cleric epic gets so much attention and causes so much heartache is that it make such a huge difference to a guild's raid capabilities.  Not their ability to kill mob X, but their ability to try mob X and not take all night recovering if they fail, or taking large breaks to rez a few dead folks because suddenly the clerics are lom.<br>
<br>
I'd venture to say that if they made Ragefire's respawn rate 1 day shorter, it wouldn't make that much difference to the way people feel about it.  For servers like mine that have Ragefire rotations, the list is months long.  The only way I could think of to &quot;fix&quot; it would to be to make Ragefire triggered on demand, which leads back to what I said about the rate of epics entering the game.<br>
<br>
While I would echo your sentiment about not liking things that make people act vicious to each other, I rather doubt SOE will decide to make Ragefire spawn daily, so I personally don't expect this situation to change significantly any time soon.<br>
<br>
I also think SOE has gotten plenty of the type of feedback you're requesting here. <p><BR>
