<br>
The following happened recently on my server.  Now remember, Verant's rules say that you can't &quot;camp&quot; Ragefire, he's free to the first group that engages him (play nice rule 1), although if he's contested then the people that are ready first get the first shot at him (play nice rule 3).<br>
<br>
Cleric A starts camping Ragefire right before a patch, then is back as soon as the servers come up.  &quot;A&quot; sits in the zone corner with her friends.<br>
<br>
Cleric B and her guild arrives, and camps right on top of Ragefire's spawn point with her guild.<br>
<br>
Cleric C shows up a day later, camping at another zone corner.<br>
<br>
When Ragefire spawns, he immediately aggros someone in B's group.  Ragefire is mezzed.  At this point, the puller for cleric A petitions that Rage has spawned, and someone needs to come watch to make sure it goes well.  A guide shows up and follows cleric A's monk for most of the rest of the encounter.<br>
<br>
Cleric C is the first to have troops ready.  When they are set to engage, they are informed that Ragefire has been engaged (mezzed) already.  Cleric B would be ready within another minute to take him, and it would be a conflict between these two groups, except at this point Talendor sweeps in and wipes everyone in both groups.  It is believe that someone from Cleric C's group ported in and aggroed Tal on the way there, inadvertently wiping both groups.<br>
<br>
At this point, only a few people from cleric A's groups were killed in the Talendor debacle, since most were still up in the zone corner.  About 15 minutes later, cleric A has the forces ready to take Ragefire.  Neither B or C are ready at this time, so A's puller (with the guide following) goes off to find Ragefire.<br>
<br>
Ragefire is found in another corner of the zone.  Cleric B's puller is kiting Ragefire around - not to bring him in for the kill, but to keep him occupied while his forces regroup.  Given that cleric B is not ready to engage and cleric A is, cleric A's puller takes Ragefire back.  Cleric A's group kills ragefire and cleric A gets the heart.<br>
<br>
A while later, after everyone has been rezzed, a GM arrives.  The GM makes cleric A destroy the loot, then places it in cleric B's inventory.  The puller for cleric A gets a warning for stealing a mob that was engaged already.<br>
-------------------------------------<br>
So what happened in summary:<br>
<br>
Cleric A was first to camp the mob, was the only group ready to engage when they did so, completed the kill, and had to destroy the loot and take a warning.<br>
<br>
Cleric B was trained by someone with cleric C, then lost the mob to cleric A while they had it in a holding pattern, and was awarded the loot without a fight.<br>
<br>
Cleric C was first ready to kill Ragefire, but didn't get the opportunity to kill or loot, likely because one of their own members wiped them out.<br>
---------------------------------------<br>
So what needs to be fixed:<br>
<br>
1. Verant must enforce its policies uniformly.  If you can't kite Lodizal around for half an hour while your forces arrive to kill him (as GMs have said before), then you can't kite Ragefire around either.  If it is ok to hold a mob while your forces arrive or buff, then say so, and deal with the two rangers who hold Ragefire for hours.<br>
<br>
2. Make Ragefire's spawn point random in the zone.  Sure, this could make him pop in a bad place.  But since he can't be &quot;camped&quot;, don't make him spawn in one place repeatedly.<br>
<br>
3. Consider perma-rooting Ragefire (the man), and making him immune to charm and mez.  This way, if you engage him, you have to kill him.  If he attacks you and you run out of his range, then he's not engaged and someone else can take him.  If you attack him but can't kill him, he'll summon and kill you unless you zone.  Of course after you zone he's not engaged anymore.<br>
-------------------------------------<br>
<br>
